overview: "The user initiated a request to fix a pull request riddled with
  issues, including critical Vercel deployment failures. The agent
  systematically addressed a comprehensive list of problems: high-severity
  security flaws like forgeable admin cookies and arbitrary API parameters,
  various functional bugs in PDF generation and form inputs, and linting errors.
  The authentication system was upgraded to use HMAC-signed sessions compatible
  with Vercel's Edge Runtime. A major hurdle was the persistent Vercel
  deployment failure, initially traced to a missing DATABASE_URL in the Prisma
  schema. Subsequently, a critical Next.js security vulnerability
  (CVE-2025-66478) necessitated an upgrade to Next.js 16. This upgrade, however,
  introduced breaking changes in Prisma (requiring schema adjustments) and
  ESLint (requiring script and configuration updates). The agent iteratively
  diagnosed and resolved these cascading issues, ensuring the application was
  secure, functional, and successfully deployable on Vercel."
